rComments: Her class is relatively straight forward. Not the most interesting content but she clearly knows it well and tries to keep it interesting with videos, etc. Always available for help when you need it. Pay attention during class and you'll ace it.

So difficult to understand, awkward lectures, relies on students' answers instead of just teaching. Flipping back and forth between slides and videos, playing 10 seconds of a video. Tests were relatively easy if you did the readings. No need to go to class, read the chapter and her powerpoint on blackboard and that's all you need.

Granted, sometimes she is difficult to understand but I think other reviewers are blowing things out of proportion. She was a decent prof. She's pretty clear about what's going to be tested so midterms and the final were so easy. Read the textbook and attend a couple of the classes, not all, and you'll still do well. Easy class.
Goes straight from her slides that are directly from textbook - no need to attend class. tests are easy but class is extremely boring and her accent can be difficult to understand sometimes.

She is not a good professor. Her slides are unorganized, and she is constantly flipping back and forth. Her exams do not reflect what the material is in the classroom, making it hard to get a good mark. I would definitely not recommend you to take a class with her if you enjoy structure, clarity and a well-spoken professor.

I really did not like this class. It was extremely boring, and her accent was strong at times. The information was interesting, unfortunately, her teaching was not. She seemed to be a very nice and considerate woman, however her teaching was not at the level it should have been at. Midterms and the final were mostly based on the slides/textbook.
Not clear what so ever. your textbook will be your friend
